HEADWORD: Felidae
<hw>Felidae</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a natural family of lithe-bodied
round-headed fissiped mammals, including the cats; wildcats; lions;
leopards; cheetahs; and saber-toothed tigers.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> family <fam>Felidae</fam>.</syn>⟦br⟧
